<paragraph id="8BFD36D586066B20FEFC8B87FB95F7D3" blockId="20.[243,1228,2035,2627]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">
Stratigraphic position. In bioclastic limestone, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B3086066B20FB498B87FE89F7D3" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="83" unit="m" value="130.0">130 m</quantity>
above the base of the Namoi Formation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586066B20FEFB843BFEAEF699" blockId="20.[243,1228,2035,2627]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">
Material. 
<specimenCount id="9D44FD5C86066B20FE39843BFD2DF7EC" box="[481,695,2127,2167]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83" type="generic">7 specimens</specimenCount>
from south-east of 'Rangari' (Locality 18), 3 from Swains Gully (Locality 25), 2 from 'Marohn' (Locality 28) and 1 from Glenbawn (Locality 29).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586066B20FEFB8573FB3FF6B4" blockId="20.[243,1228,2035,2627]" box="[291,1189,2311,2351]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">Geographic distribution. 'Rangari' to Glenbawn.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586066B20FEFC8542FBD9F6C6" blockId="20.[243,1228,2035,2627]" box="[292,1091,2358,2397]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">Geological age. Middle to late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586066B20FEFB8511FDB4F5D8" blockId="20.[243,1228,2035,2627]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">
Remarks. The figured specimens resemble the 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786066B20FBE28511FB50F610" box="[1082,1226,2405,2443]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686066B20FF2C85E6FE5CF622" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1881" box="[244,454,2450,2489]" class="Gastropoda" family="Neritopsidae" genus="Turbonitella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cycloneritimorpha" pageId="20" pageNumber="83" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786066B20FF2C85E6FE5CF622" box="[244,454,2450,2489]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">Turbonitella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
biserialis(Phillips) designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B2486066B20FB8F85E6FEF8F67C" author="Knight, J. B." pageId="20" pageNumber="83" refId="ref26100" refString="Knight, J. B., 1941. Paleozoic gastropod genotypes. Geological Society of America, Special papers 32, 510 pp. 32 figs, 96 pIs." type="book" year="1941">Knight (1941)</bibRefCitation>
in being a turbiniform with strong collabral ribs on shoulder, but differs in lacking a row of ribs on the lower whorl face.
</paragraph>
